<storykicker><![CDATA[India has about 18.4 million people living in modern slavery. Here is the list of top 10 countries and the number of people in modern slavery today.]]></storykicker>
<storybody><![CDATA[<p>Modern slavery or contemporary slavery refers to the institutions or form of slavery that continue to exist in the present day. 2016 studies show that estimated 45.8 million people are enslaved in the world today, which include men, women and children. The count is 28 per cent more than previously estimated.<br /></p><p>The modern slavery or the form of slavery existing today include practices like forced labour, bonded labour, human trafficking, worst forms of child labour, descent-based slavery, forced and early marriage, and exploitation of migrant workers in conditions amounting to slavery. <br /></p>According to the Global Slavery Index 2016, India has topped the list of the 50 countries with the largest number of people in modern slavery, as of 2016. The country with a population of 1,311,051,000 people has about 18.4 million people living in modern slavery. <br /><p><b>Here is the list of top 10 countries and the number of people in modern slavery, as of 2016:</b></p><p>{mosimage}</p><p>{mosimage}&nbsp;</p><p>The Global Slavery Index is a country by country estimation of the number of people living in modern slavery today. </p><p>Interested in General Knowledge and Current Affairs?<b> <a target="_blank" href="http://indiatoday.intoday.in/education/categorylist/current-affairs/1/908.html" mce_href="http://indiatoday.intoday.in/education/categorylist/current-affairs/1/908.html">Click here</a></b>  to stay informed and know what is happening around the world with our <b>G.K. and Current Affairs section</b>.&nbsp; <br /></p>]]></storybody>
